Problem 1¶

1. Creating signals¶

In [1]:
class pwld_interp1d:
    def __init__(self, x, y, sigma=1.):
        n = len(x)
        dy = np.random.normal(0, sigma, n)
        self.y = np.stack([y + dy, y]).flatten('F')
        self.x = np.stack([x, x]).flatten('F')
        self.interp = interp1d(self.x, self.y, kind='linear')
    
    def __call__(self, y):
        return self.interp(y)
In [2]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.interpolate import interp1d

%matplotlib inline

x1 = np.linspace(0, 150, 20)
y1 = x1**(1/2)*np.sin(x1)

x2_1 = np.linspace(0, 150, 20)
y2_1 = np.tan(x2_1)
x2 = np.stack([x2_1, x2_1]).flatten('F')
y2_d = np.random.normal(0, 0.5, len(x2_1))
y2 = np.stack([y2_1 + y2_d, y2_1]).flatten('F')

x3 = np.linspace(0, 150, 20)
y3 = x3**(1/3)*np.cos(x3)

f1 = interp1d(x1, y1, kind='linear')
y1_new = f1(x1)

f2 = interp1d(x2, y2,kind='linear')
y2_new = f2(x2)

f3 = interp1d(x3, y3, kind='quadratic')
y3_new = f3(x3)

3. Recovery procedure¶

In [5]:
n = x_new.shape[0]
D1 = np.zeros((n-1,n))
i,j = np.indices(D1.shape)
D1[i==j] = 1.
D1[i==j-1] = -1.

D2 = np.zeros((n-2,n))
i,j = np.indices(D2.shape)
D2[i==j] = 1.
D2[i==j-1] = -2.
D2[i==j-2] = 1.

Comment: We can see that for each signal and penalty there is a point after which penalty is constant while residual is growing. We need to get a point where both the residual and penalty are minimized, the point of inflection is the point of minimum sum of them, so the best gamma is there for each case.

Problem 2¶

From $$ \epsilon=\{x: (x-c)^T P^{-1} (x-c) \leq 1\} $$

we can get $$\Rightarrow$$

$$ \epsilon=\{x : 1 - (x-c)^T P^{-1} (x-c) \geq 0\} $$

which is Schur-comlement of P for matrix $\begin{pmatrix}1 & (x - c)^T\\(x - c) & P\end{pmatrix}$

Finally we put $a$ in it and get Linear Matrix Inequality:

$$ \begin{pmatrix} 1 & (a-c)^T\\ a-c & P \end{pmatrix} \succeq 0 $$

3. Goemans-Williamson approximation.¶

In [33]:
cholesky = np.linalg.cholesky(X.value + np.identity(n)*1e-1)

gw_value = np.zeros(1000)
for i in range(gw_value.shape[0]):
    cut = np.random.normal(size=n)
    cut_chol = cholesky @ cut
    cut_chol[cut_chol>0] = 1
    cut_chol[cut_chol<=0] = -1
    gw_value[i] = cut_chol.T @ laplacian @ cut_chol

Problem 4¶

1. Formulate the above problem as a linear program¶

Let $x_{ij}$ be the tonns of cargo, where the raw index $i=1,2,3,4$ for $C1,C2,C3,C4$ and column index $j$ - compartment, $j=1$ - Front, $j=2$ - Centre, $j=3$ - Rear.

The constaints of the problem are:

  • limited cargo:
$$x_{11}+x_{12}+x_{13}<=18 $$$$x_{21}+x_{22}+x_{23}<=15$$$$x_{31}+x_{32}+x_{33}<=23$$$$x_{41}+x_{42}+x_{43}<=12$$
  • maximum weight capacity of every compartment:
$$x_{11}+x_{21}+x_{31}+x_{41}<=10$$$$x_{12}+x_{22}+x_{32}+x_{42}<=16$$$$x_{13}+x_{23}+x_{33}+x_{43}<=8$$
  • maximum space capacity of every compartment:
$$480 x_{11}+650 x_{21}+580 x_{31}+390 x_{41}<=6800$$$$480 x_{12}+650 x_{22}+580 x_{32}+390 x_{42}<=8700$$$$480 x_{13}+650 x_{23}+580 x_{33}+390 x_{43}<=5300$$
  • plane balance:
$$\frac{{x}_{11}+{x}_{21}+{x}_{31}+{x}_{41}}{10}=\frac{{x}_{12}+{x}_{22}+{x}_{32}+{x}_{42}}{16}=\frac{{x}_{13}+{x}_{23}+{x}_{33}+{x}_{43}}{8}$$

The objective function:

We need to maximize total profit:

$$ \text{ max } 310\left[{x}_{11}+{x}_{12}+ {x}_{13}\right]+380\left[{x}_{21}+ {x}_{22}+ {x}_{23}\right]+350\left[ {x}_{31}+ {x}_{32}+ {x}_{33}\right]+285\left[ {x}_{41}+ {x}_{42}+ {x}_{43}\right] $$

2. What assumptions are made in formulating this problem as a linear program?¶

  • The data is accurate
  • We are told we can split the cargoes into any fractions that we want and between any compartments
  • Any cargo can be packed into any compartment

3. Solve the problem¶

Comment:

We can see that only the weight change of C2 affected the maximum profit, when we increase the weight by 10%, the profit is bigger (12211), while we decrease by 10%, the profit is lower (12091).

The reason for that you can see above in the rounded result of x, where the components of C2 = [9,0,6] are fully used, so we pack the whole 15/15 tonnes of C2, beacuse it has the highest 380 dollar/tonnes. The second one is C3=[1,13,2], where we use 17/23 tonnes with 350 dollar/tonnes. So, that why 10 percent change does not affect the result for the rest, because they do not contribute to the shipment. Even if we put the weight 1000 for C1, nothing will change.
